			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="pl">
					<!--<p>Relacja <persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Mirki Wiener</persName> (sygn. 301/1169)</p>
      <p>Oryginał, rękopis, 4 strony, 210 x 295 mm, język polski</p>-->
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>
						<orgName ref="#ehri_et_voivodships_historical_commission">Wojewódzka Komisja Historyczna</orgName></p>
					<p>W <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublinie</placeName></p>
					<p>Dnia <date when="1945-11-15">15.XI.1945</date></p>
					<p>Zeznaje do protokołu</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Mirka Wiener</persName></p>
					<p>Urodzona <date when="1932-02-04">4.II.1932</date></p>
					<p>Tatuowana w <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Oświęcimiu</placeName> nr A 3977</p>
					<p>Uczennica</p>
					<p>Przed <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">wojną</term> zamieszkała w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżycach</placeName> pod <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html"
							>Lublinem</placeName></p>
					<p>Obecnie <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lubartowska 8 m. 12</placeName></p>
					<p>Ma matkę; córka kupca</p>
					<p>Protokolant: <persName ref="#ehri_et_szajowicz_irena">Irena Szajowicz</persName>; kierownik Komisji Historycznej w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublinie</placeName></p>
					<p>Mieszkałam w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżycach</placeName>, gdy <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Niemcy</term> weszli w <date when="1939">1939 roku</date> do Polski. Komendantem miasta był <term
							ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Niemiec</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_engel">Engel</persName>. Baliśmy się go okropnie, gdyż <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">bił</term> i strzelał. Nieraz wpadał do mieszkań i <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">zabijał</term> całe <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodziny</term>. Taki los spotkał <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodzinę</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel">Silbernadel</persName>: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-820" type="subject">ojca</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_kuna_herisch">Kunę Herisch</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-820" type="subject">synów</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_usze">Usze</persName> i <persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_jankiel">Jankiel</persName> za to, że <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1051" type="subject">sprzedawali</term> mięso. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">Kradł</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">rabował</term> też wszystko z mieszkań żydowskich. Kilka razy w tygodniu przyjeżdżali <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1124" type="subject">żandarmi</term> z sąsiedniej miejscowości, odległej 10 kilometrów – <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764000/niedrzwica-duza.html">Niedźwice</placeName>. Kazali sobie <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">dawać</term> pieniądze, auta, konie. Mieli ciągle inne <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">żądania</term>. Zaczęło się od „<term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">kontrybucji</term>” 20000 złotych, a później <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">żądali</term> coraz więcej. Raz przyjechali <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-mani</term> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublina</placeName> i zabrali 400 mężczyzn na <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560"
							type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>, a wiele osób <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">zginęło</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">zastrzeleni</term> przez <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>. W <date when="1941">1941</date> roku <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">zabrali</term> kilkaset <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">mężczyzn</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">kobiet</term> do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560"
							type="camp">Majdanka</placeName>. W <date when="1942">1942</date> roku pewnego wtorku przyjechali <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1126" type="subject">Ukraińcy</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
							type="subject">SS-owcy</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">Strzelali</term> do ludzi i zabierali, <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_02.jpg" n="2"/> a po tym ładowali do <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">wagonów</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">wywieźli</term> do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032"
							type="camp">Treblinki</placeName>. Myśmy się <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-365" type="subject">ukrywali</term>; w <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-365" type="subject">skrytce</term> pod podłogą była zrobiona
						jama. Było to w mieszkaniu mojego <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-820" type="subject">kuzyna</term>. Było 50 osób. Było okropnie duszno, tak że jedno <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-112" type="subject">dziecko</term>
						dwuletnie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">umarło</term> wskutek braku powietrza. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">Akcja</term> trwała prawie 2 dni. Gdyśmy wyszli złapali nas
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-mani</term> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764000/niedrzwica-duza.html">Niedwiedzic</placeName>, którzy przeszukiwali mieszkania żydowskie; rozwalali piece, zrywali podłogi i
						tak dalej. Nas zamknięto w <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">bóżnicy</term>. Po jednym dniu udało nam się <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">uciec</term>. Po tym <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-owcy</term> zażądali po 20000zł od <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodziny</term>; za to zrobią <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">obóz</term> i nas nie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">zabiją</term>, tylko będziemy <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracować</term>.</p>
					<p>Komendantem był <persName ref="#ehri_et_hess">Hess</persName>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">Obóz</term> był otoczony drutami i tylko <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-566" type="subject">żydowska
							milicja</term> nas pilnowała. <persName ref="#ehri_et_hess">Hess</persName> nie znęcał się specjalnie. Po prawie 9 miesiącach przyjechał <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">SS-owiec</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> z <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">gestapowcami</orgName>. 500 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">kobiet</term> z <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">dziećmi</term> zostało <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zabitych</term>, a pozostałych 100 i <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">mężczyzn</term> zabrali do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp">Budzynia</placeName>. Ja uratowałam się w ten sposób, że wmieszałam się do grupy
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">przeznaczonej</term> do wyjazdu.</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> był komendantem <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">obozu</term> w <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp">Budzyniu</placeName>,
						gdzie znajdowali się już Żydzi z innych miasteczek: z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/767623/krasnik.html">Kraśnika</placeName>, a nawet <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warszawy</placeName>. Było nas razem około 5000 ludzi. Tutaj pilnowali
						nas już <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-owcy</term>. Codziennie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">ginęli</term> ludzie. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">Umierali</term> z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">głodu</term> (otrzymywaliśmy bochenek <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">chleba</term> na 10 osób; <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">zupa</term> była rzadka, a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">ziemniaki</term> surowe). Co pewien czas były <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selekcje</term>; wybierano słabszych i <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">dzieci</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">strzelano</term> z karabinów maszynowych. <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_03.jpg" n="3"/> Przedtem
						musieli sami wykopać sobie groby, w których ich pozostali grzebali. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">Tyfus plamisty</term> dziesiątkował ludzi. Ja <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
							type="subject">pracowałam</term> w kuchni. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Kobiety</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracowały</term> w osiedlu <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">niemieckim</term> oraz w fabrykach amunicji i samolotów. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826"
							type="subject">Mężczyźni</term> we fabrykach i przy budowie dróg. Było nam bardzo źle. Specjalnie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">znęcał się</term> nad nami <persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> i <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-owiec Oberscharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_mohr_otto">Mohe</persName>.</p>
					<p>Po roku ubrali nas w <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">pasiaki</term> i odstawiono do nowego <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">obozu</term> zwanego Barakenbau; był przy <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp">Budzyniu</placeName>, a podlegał <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdankowi</placeName>. Komendantem był <persName ref="#ehri_et_leipold_josef"
							>Leipold</persName>. On i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-owiec</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_jungfleisch">Jungfleisch</persName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">Unterscharführer</term> oraz <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">Oberscharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_kleist_wilhelm">Willi Kleist</persName> bili, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">strzelali</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">znęcali się</term>
						nieludzko. <persName ref="#ehri_et_leipold_josef">Leipold</persName> za byle przewinienie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">wieszał</term> w baraku u pułapu za nogi, głową w dół. Ofiary wisiały po kilka godzin i niejeden <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zginął</term> w ten sposób.</p>
					<p>Z <foreign xml:lang="de">Barakenbau</foreign> zabrano nas po jakimś czasie. Nie umiem dokładnie określić terminu do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanka</placeName>. W <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanku</placeName> nie było mi specjalnie źle. Gdy <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Armia Czerwona</orgName> się zbliżyła, wprowadzili nas <term
							ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Niemcy</term> do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/774069/cmielow.html">Ćmielowa</placeName>; 170 km <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">szliśmy</term> piechotą. Kto nie miał sił,
						został <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zastrzelony</term>. 8 dni <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">gnano</term> nas w deszczu i prawie bez <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">jedzenia</term>. W <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/774069/cmielow.html">Ćmielowie</placeName> załadowano nas do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522"
							type="subject">pociągów</term> i zawieziono do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Oświęcimia</placeName>. Wybito nam numery i przeznaczono od razu do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
							type="subject">pracy</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">Pracowałam</term> na B <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">lagrze</term> w <foreign xml:lang="de"
							>Strassenkomando</foreign>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">Pracowałam</term> bardzo ciężko. Podałam, że mam 16 lat, by się ratować. Musiałam więc <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
							type="subject">pracować</term> jak dorośli. Były ciągle <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_04.jpg" n="4"/>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selekcje</term>, ale ja uciekałam wtedy. Po tym, w <date when="1944">jesieni</date> była wielka <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selekcja</term>.
						Wiele <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">kobiet</term> poszło do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">komory</term>, a reszta – wśród nich i ja – wysłana do <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen Bergen</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Jechaliśmy tydzień. Wśród strasznych <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">warunków</term> i o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">głodzie</term>. W <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen Bergen</placeName> mieszkaliśmy w <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">namiotach</term>. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">Marzliśmy</term> okrutnie i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">mokliśmy</term> na deszczach. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Jedzenia</term> też było bardzo mało. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000228">Kremer</persName> przyjechał później, a także <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Lagerältester</foreign></term> z <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Oświęcimia</placeName>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_starostka_stanislawa">Stenia</persName>, która się okropnie nad nami <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">znęcała</term>. Wiele <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1126"
							type="subject">SS-manek</term> z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">Oświęcimia</term> i bardzo dokuczały, lecz nazwisk nie pamiętam. Nie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"
							>pracowałyśmy</term>. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000228">Krämer</persName> wprowadził okropny rygor i zapanowały stosunki gorsze jak w <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp"
							>Oświęcimiu</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Po tym wyjechałyśmy z 500 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">kobietami</term> do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2850894/raguhn.html">Raguhn</placeName> koło <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2937959/dessau.html"
							>Dessau</placeName>. Tam <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracowałyśmy</term> w fabryce amunicji bardzo ciężko. Okropnie znęcała się nad nami <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject"
							>Aufseherka</term>
						<persName ref="ehri_et_lanni">Lanni</persName> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1126" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Unterscharführer</foreign></term>, którego nazwiska nie pamiętam. <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004289">Amerykanie</orgName> się zbliżali. Załadowano nas na auta i 2 tygodnie nas <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">wożono</term>. Bili nas i okropnie się znęcali, a
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">jeść</term> prawie nie dawali. W końcu dotarliśmy do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="camp">Teresienstadt</placeName>, gdzie miałyśmy zostać
						spalone. Było tam 60000 ludzi. Komendant zwrócił się do <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-419">Czerwonego Krzyża</orgName>, że jeśli jemu, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">żonie</term> jego i
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">dziecku</term> daruje się życie, on rozkazu nie wykona i ludzi nie spali. <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-419">Czerwony Krzyż</orgName> sprawę załatwił i w
						ten sposób zostaliśmy uratowani.</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Winer Mirka</persName></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<!--<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Mirka Winer</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/1169)</p>
      <p>Original, manuscript, 4 pages, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>-->
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>
						<orgName ref="#ehri_et_voivodships_historical_commission">Voivodship’s Historical Commission</orgName></p>
					<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName></p>
					<p>On <date when="1945-11-15">15 November 1945</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Mirka Winer</persName></p>
					<p>Testifies for the record</p>
					<p>Born <date when="1932-02-04">4 February 1932</date></p>
					<p>Tatooed number A 3977 in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName></p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">Student</term></p>
					<p>Before the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> she resided in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html"
							>Lublin</placeName></p>
					<p>Presently in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">8 Lubartowska Street apt. 12</placeName></p>
					<p>Has mother; a merchant’s daughter</p>
					<p>Record taken by: <persName ref="#ehri_et_szajowicz_irena">Irena Szajowicz</persName>; Head of <orgName ref="#ehri_et_historical_commission_in_lublin">Historical Commission in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName></orgName></p>
					<p>I was living in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> when <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> entered Poland in <date when="1939">1939</date>. The commandant for the town was a <term
							ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">German</term> named <persName ref="#ehri_et_engel">Engel</persName>. We were terribly afraid of him, because he used to beat and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject"
							>shoot</term> people. He would invade a flat and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">kill</term> whole <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term>. That’s what happened to
						the <persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel">Silbernadel</persName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-820" type="subject">family</term>: father <persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_kuna_herisch">Kuna Herisch</persName>, sons <persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_usze">Usze</persName> and <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_jankiel">Jankiel</persName> for trading meat. He also stole and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">plundered</term> Jewish flats. A few times a week <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1124" type="subject">gendarmes</term> would come from a neighbouring town 10 kilometres away – <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764000/niedrzwica-duza.html">Niedźwice</placeName>. They had us give them money,
						autos, horses. They kept making new demands. It all started with a <q>contribution</q> of 20000 zlotys, and then they just kept demanding more. Once <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> came from <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> and took 400 men to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>, many people <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
							type="subject">died</term> then, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>. In <date when="1941">1941</date> they took
						several hundred <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> to <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>. One Tuesday in <date when="1942">1942</date>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1126" type="subject">Ukrainians</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> came. They shot at people and took people away, <pb
							facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_02.jpg" n="2"/> loaded them into <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">train cars</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">transported</term> to
							<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName>. We stayed hidden, in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hideout</term> under the floor there was a pit. It was in
						my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">cousin</term>’s flat. There were 50 people there. It was terribly stuffy, so stuffy that one 2-year old <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject"
							>child</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> of lack of air. The action went on for almost 2 days. After we went out, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> from
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764000/niedrzwica-duza.html">Niedźwice</placeName>, who were searching Jewish flats, caught us; they smashed furnaces, ripped off floorboards and so forth. We were locked up in a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term>. After one day we managed to escape. Later, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> demanded 20000 per <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> in return for making a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> and not <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killing</term> us but making us <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>.</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_hess">Hess</persName> was the commandant. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was fenced with wire and we were guarded only by <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-566" type="subject">Jewish militia</term>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_hess">Hess</persName> didn’t torment us too much. Almost 9 months later an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
							type="subject">SS-man</term> named <persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> came with <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> officers. 500 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825"
							type="subject">women</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> and the remaining 100 and the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> were taken to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp">Budzyń</placeName>. I was saved because I mingled with the group who’d been <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selected</term> to go.</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> was commandant for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp"
							>Budzyń</placeName>, where at that time there were already Jews from other towns: from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/767623/krasnik.html">Kraśnik</placeName>, even [from] <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. There was a
						total of about 5000 of us. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> kept guard there. People <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> every day. They <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term> (we were given a loaf of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> between 10 people; the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">soup</term> was thin and the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potatoes</term> raw). From time to time <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selections</term> took place; the weaker and the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selected</term> and machine guns were fired. <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_03.jpg" n="3"/>
						Beforehand they had to dig their own graves, where the others buried them in later. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">Typhus fever</term> decimated people. I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
							type="subject">worked</term> in the kitchen. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Women</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> in the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">German</term> estate and in ammunition and plane plants. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">Men</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> in plants and built roads. Our plight was very miserable. <persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> and an <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS Oberscharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_mohr_otto">Mohe</persName> were especially cruel.</p>
					<p>A year later they dressed us in striped <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">uniforms</term> and moved to a new <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> named Barakenbau; it was
						located near <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp">Budzyń</placeName>, but administered by <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>. <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_leipold_josef">Leipold</persName> was the commandant. He and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS Unterscharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_jungfleisch">Jungfleisch</persName> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">Oberscharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_kleist_wilhelm">Willi Kleist</persName> beat, shot and tormented us inhumanly. <persName ref="#ehri_et_leipold_josef">Leipold</persName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">hanged</term> people head down from the barracks ceiling for any petty offence. The victims hung like this for several hours and many <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> like this.</p>
					<p>Some time later we were moved from Barakenbau. I can’t put an exact date on <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>. In <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp"
							>Majdanek</placeName> I wasn’t all that miserable. When the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Red Army</orgName> approached, <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> moved us to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/774069/cmielow.html">Ćmielów</placeName>; we <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">walked</term> 170 kilometres on foot. Those who couldn’t make it were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term>. For 8 days we were driven in rain with almost no <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food.</term> In <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/774069/cmielow.html">Ćmielów</placeName> we were loaded onto <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">trains</term> and taken to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0"
							type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>. We had numbers embossed and wee directed to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> right away. I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"
							>worked</term> in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">lager</term>
						<note type="gloss">Lager – (Ger.) camp</note> B in <foreign xml:lang="de">Strassenkommando</foreign>. I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> very hard. I had claimed I was 16 to save myself. And so I had to <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> like adults. They kept making <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_04.jpg" n="4"/>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selections</term>, but I ran away every time. Later, in <date when="1944">autumn</date> there was a major <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject"
							>selection</term>. A lot of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> were sent to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">chamber</term>, and the rest – including me –
						[were] sent to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen Bergen</placeName>.</p>
					<p>The journey took a week. In terrible <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">conditions</term> and we suffered <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term>. In <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen Bergen</placeName> we lived in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">tents</term>. We would freeze terribly and get wet in the rain. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Food</term> was scarce. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000228">Krämer</persName> arrived later on, as did <foreign xml:lang="de">Lagerältester</foreign>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_starostka_stanislawa">Stenia</persName> from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>, who was terribly cruel to us. [There were] plenty of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-women</term> from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName> and they molested us very much, but I forget the names. We did not
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000228">Krämer</persName> introduced strict rigour and relations deteriorated to a state worse than in
							<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Next, we left with 500 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2850894/raguhn.html">Raguhn</placeName> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2937959/dessau.html"
							>Dessau</placeName>. We did very hard <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in an ammunition plant there. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480" type="subject">Aufseherin</term>
						<persName ref="ehri_et_lanni">Lanni</persName> and <foreign xml:lang="de">Unterscharführer</foreign>, whose name I can’t remember, molested us dreadfully. <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_americans" type="subject">Americans</term> were coming closer. We were loaded up onto
						auto and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">transported</term> around for two weeks. They beat and kicked us terribly and gave almost no <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
							>food</term>. Finally, we arrived in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName> where we were to be burnt. There were 60000 people there. The commandant pledged with the <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-419">Red Cross</orgName> to spare his and his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">wife</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824"
							type="subject">child</term>’s lives if he would disobey the order and not burn the people. The <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-419">Red Cross</orgName> took care of that and that’s how we were saved.</p>
					<p>[signature] <persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Winer Mirka</persName></p>
				</div>
			</div>
